      <processinfo id="aspace_41f71767eb06252e8c7f2978186bfcfa">
         <head>Processing Information</head>
         <p>Yale University records are arranged and described at the accession level by the creating office. The University Archives creates collection level descriptive records, but typically does no further arrangement and description at the accession level.</p>  
      </processinfo>
      <scopecontent id="aspace_f49744ae46c1e5880d3cd103c553d958">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>The records consist of correspondence, minutes, annual reports, faculty profiles, and administrative files of the chairman documenting the activities and operations of the Yale Department of Microbiology, which no longer exists as a separate academic unit.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
      <arrangement id="aspace_76036aebef12d43ba59f99dba1928fbe">
         <head>Arrangement</head>
         <p>The records are arranged by alphabetically by subject.</p>  
      </arrangement>
